The paper deals with natural language processing and data analysis, which are both relevant to the computer science sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also focuses on parsing and querying tabular data, which falls under the sub-category of Databases (cs.DB). The use of semantic rules and neural-based models for parsing and optimization is related to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also involves information retrieval techniques for efficient inference, which is relevant to Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
